metadata.name: “Winds of Change”
metadata.description:
In Iran, a land of ancient ways,
The winds of change now blow and sway.
For women there, the veil's demand
Has long suppressed their right to stand.
But now they rise, with voices strong,
Defying laws that kept them wronged.
Their courage shines, a beacon bright,
For freedom's cause, they stand and fight.
Yet other battles must be won,
For all who seek to live as one.
For human rights and justice fair,
Are hopes that all of us can share.
May we support and stand beside,
The brave who fight, and will not hide.
May their dreams of freedom soar and fly,
And light the path for all to try.
